# .trivyignore — reviewed and accepted CVE allowlist
#
# This file is the escape hatch for the now-blocking Trivy publish-path gate in
# .github/workflows/docker-publish.yml (Trivy scan - Backend), which fails the
# release on any fixable CRITICAL CVE (`exit-code: 1`, `severity: CRITICAL`,
# `ignore-unfixed: true`).
#
# List one CVE ID per line (e.g. `CVE-2024-12345`). A line here means the CVE
# has been reviewed and consciously accepted — typically an unfixable
# base-image CVE Trivy still flags as fixable, or a CVE in a code path the
# image does not exercise.
#
# Discipline:
#   - Every addition MUST be reviewed (a CVE silenced here is a CVE we ship).
#   - Prefer upgrading the affected layer/dependency over adding an entry.
#   - Keep a short justification comment above each ID and reassess on each
#     release so stale acceptances do not accumulate.
#
# (Empty by default — no CVEs are currently accepted.)
